% You are an expert Python engineer.
% Implement SQLAlchemy async database models for InvoiceIQ.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
1. Invoice table with fields: id (UUID, PK), file_name (str),
   file_type (str), status (enum: pending/extracted/reviewed/exported),
   vendor_name (str|null), invoice_number (str|null),
   invoice_date (date|null), due_date (date|null),
   subtotal (Decimal|null), tax (Decimal|null), total (Decimal|null),
   currency (str, default USD), line_items (JSON),
   confidence_scores (JSON), exported_at (datetime|null),
   created_at (datetime, auto UTC)
2. Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 async declarative base
3. Provide async engine and session factory
4. Include alembic-compatible Base for migrations
5. All Decimal fields use Numeric(10,2)